 <!-- Introduction -->
 <!-- The introduction should start as shown: -->
 <purpose>
   <p>
     This part of ISO 10303 specifies an application module for the
     representation of the cross sectional shape of an extruded structure perpendicular to the local centre line.
     The structure is defined in a recursive way consisting of a main group and one or more sub-groups.
     For each group and each leaf the minimum and maximum cross sectional diameter can be defined and also the minimum bend radius.
     A group can be twisted and if so the twist direction (clockwise or counterclockwise) and twist period can be specified. 
     A group can be formed by a tubular covering or by lacing. 
   </p>
 </purpose>

